  "prompt": "Does the TV show Gotham share the same universe with Arrow and The Flash?",
  "response": "No, the TV show \"Gotham\" does not share the same universe with \"Arrow\" and \"The Flash.\" \"Arrow\" and \"The Flash\" are part of the Arrowverse, a shared universe created by DC Comics and The CW. \n\n\"Gotham,\" on the other hand, is part of its own separate continuity created by Fox. It focuses on the early years of several Batman characters, including James Gordon and Bruce Wayne. While both are based on DC Comics properties, they exist in distinct and separate television universes.",
